<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Sedimentation" class="currentChild" href="Sedimentation">Sedimentation</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A problem of <a title="Gravure" href="Gravure">gravure</a> inks characterized by the settling of the solid ink <a title="Pigment" href="Pigment">pigment</a> out of the fluid <a title="Vehicle" href="Vehicle">vehicle</a> as a result of long-term storage. Frequent agitation of the ink container may help alleviate the problem. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
Inks possessing higher <a title="Viscosity" href="Viscosity">viscosity</a> (even the "false viscosity" characteristic of <a title="Thixotropic" href="Thixotropic">thixotropic</a> inks) will be less susceptible to sedimentation than thinner inks, and inks produced with larger and/or more poorly dispersed pigment particles will be more susceptible to sedimentation. (See also <a title="Flocculation" href="Flocculation">Flocculation</a>.) 
</p>
<div style="clear: both;"></div></div>


